## What happened

In .NET 11, `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on **macOS**. This is a documented breaking change (dotnet/runtime#119182, milestoned 11.0.0, tagged `breaking-change`).

**Root cause:** Apple's Security Transforms framework never natively supported DSA. Previous .NET versions provided an OpenSSL-based fallback on macOS, but .NET 11 removed it — aligning macOS with iOS/tvOS, which already blocked DSA. DSA (FIPS 186-4) is considered cryptographically weak; NIST deprecated it in favor of ECDSA/EdDSA.

## How to fix

You have three options, in order of recommendation:

### Option 1 — Use `DSAOpenSsl` explicitly (macOS with Homebrew OpenSSL)

```csharp
using System.Security.Cryptography;

// Requires OpenSSL installed (e.g. brew install openssl)
// Only works on Linux/macOS-with-OpenSSL, NOT on Windows
if (OperatingSystem.IsMacOS() || OperatingSystem.IsLinux())
{
    using var dsa = new DSAOpenSsl();
    dsa.ImportParameters(savedParams);
    bool valid = dsa.VerifyData(data, signature, HashAlgorithmName.SHA256);
}
```

> ⚠️ `DSAOpenSsl` requires OpenSSL to be discoverable at runtime (set `DOTNET_SYSTEM_SECURITY_CRYPTOGRAPHY_OPENSSLLIBRARYPATH` if needed).

### Option 2 — Use BouncyCastle (fully cross-platform, recommended)

```bash
dotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography
```

```csharp
using Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;
using Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Signers;
using Org.BouncyCastle.Security;

// Import your key
var pubKey = DotNetUtilities.GetDsaPublicKey(savedParams);
var signer = SignerUtilities.GetSigner("SHA256withDSA");
signer.Init(forSigning: false, pubKey);
signer.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);
bool valid = signer.VerifySignature(signature);
```

### Option 3 — Migrate to ECDSA (long-term fix)

If you control the signing side, re-sign with ECDSA or Ed25519 (new in .NET 11). DSA should only be retained for verifying legacy signatures you can't re-generate.

### Summary

| Approach | Cross-platform | Effort | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `DSAOpenSsl` | Linux + macOS (w/ OpenSSL) | Low | Needs OpenSSL on macOS |
| BouncyCastle | ✅ All | Medium | Managed impl, no native deps |
| Migrate to ECDSA/Ed25519 | ✅ All | High | Best long-term solution |
